<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Carbuncle" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Carbuncle,</orth> 1) a precious stone of deep red colour: <bibl n="shak. err 3.2.138" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 2, 138</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.4.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 4, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.485" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 485</bibl>. <cit><quote>had it been a c. of Phoebus' wheel,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.189" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 189</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) a gangrenous ulcer: <cit><quote>a plague-sore, an embossed c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 2.4.227" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 4, 227</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>